    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> ginger</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-drunken-noodles/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>rice noodles</strong> to a large bowl, cover them with <strong>boiled water </strong>and set aside to soak for 10-12 min or until the noodles are tender</p><p>Once tender, drain the\u00a0noodles, reserving a cup of the\u00a0<strong>starchy noodle water</strong></p><p>Tip: Drizzle the noodles with a little\u00a0vegetable oil to stop them from sticking together</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-drunken-noodles/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non stick) with a drizzle of\u00a0<strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Once softened, add the\u00a0<strong>chopped ginger\u00a0</strong>and\u00a0<strong>garlic\u00a0</strong>and cook further for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-drunken-noodles/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the\u00a0<strong>pork mince</strong> to the pan with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 5-7 min or until the pork\u00a0has browned and beginning to crisp, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-drunken-noodles/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the pork is cooking, trim, then chop the <strong>spring onions</strong> into quarters</p><p>Chop the roots from the <strong>pak choi</strong> and separate the leaves, discarding the roots</p><p>Chop any larger leaves in half</p><p>Once the pork has browned, add the <strong>chopped\u00a0pak choi\u00a0</strong>and\u00a0<strong>sliced spring onion\u00a0</strong>to the pan\u00a0with a splash of\u00a0<strong>starchy noodle water</strong>\u00a0and cook for 3-4 min or until they're softened</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-drunken-noodles/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst everything is cooking, chop the<strong> coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Chop the <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Slice the\u00a0<strong>red chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]\u00a0</span></strong>finely\u00a0(scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon if you can't handle the heat!)</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-drunken-noodles/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Roll the <strong>lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut in half</p><p>Once the vegetables have softened, add the <strong>soy sauce </strong>to the pan with \u00a0the <strong>juice</strong> of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lime</strong>, the\u00a0<strong>chopped</strong> <strong>herbs </strong>and\u00a0<strong>drained noodles</strong>\u00a0and give everything a good mix up \u2013 these are your <strong>drunken noodles</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lime\u00a0</strong>into wedges</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-drunken-noodles/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the\u00a0<strong>drunken noodles\u00a0</strong>in bowls</p><p>Garnish with a <strong>lime wedge</strong> and\u00a0<strong>sliced\u00a0chilli </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
